  "text": "1. Introduction. Singular integrals and nonlocal operators have been an active area of research in different branches of mathematics such as operator theory and harmonic analysis (see [CITATION_1] ). In addition, they have received significant attention because of their strong connection with real-world problems, since they constitute a fundamental part of the modeling and simulation of complex phenomena that span vastly different length scales.",
